dct_description_sm: Scale: 1:250000;  Projection: Lambert conical orthomorphic projection;  Map Type: lcgft;  Other Descriptive Notes about Map Series: Relief shown by contours, gradient tints, and spot heights.  Five classes of roads and four classes of railroads are shown.  Covers area north from Kuttenberg (Kutna Hora) to Neubistritz [Nová Bystřice] to the south, and west from Mühlhausen (Milevsko) to Bystritz am Pernstein (Bystřice n. Pernštýnem [Bystřice nad Pernštejnem]) to the east. Humpoletz [Humpolec] roughly at center of sheet. Iglau (Jihlava) roughly below center right of sheet.  Sheet O 50, Jihlava (Iglau) from set that includes various issues of some sheets, some by various survey units of the Allied Forces (A.F.) some reissued by U.S. Army Map Service, some sheets, G.S.G.S. 4346; some sheets A.M.S. M508 (G.S.G.S. 4346).  For use by War and Navy Department Agencies only. Not for sale or distribution..  Heights in metres..  Certain main spot heights are indicated by a white tab to improve legibility..  Military grid.  Spheroid: Du Plessis..  Includes Convergence for corners of this sheet, To give a grid reference on this sheet, Grid data, Index to adjoining sheets, Conversion graph, Glossary, Authorities, and Incidence of grid letters. Also includes print color control bar in upper margin.  6-44..
dct_isPartOf_sm: Field Maps of Colonel Roland T. Fenton
